dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya lbw b Gayle 27 (41b 2x4 0x6 56m) SR: 65.85

dismissalComment.html: And Utseya falls and ZImbabwe have folded up for a meagre 85. He went for a pull  but missed.

headshotImage.caption: Carlton Baugh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Carlton Baugh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tafadzwa Mufambisi c †Baugh b Taylor 18 (31b 2x4 0x6 41m) SR: 58.06

dismissalComment.html: short delivery gets him a wicket! Banged in short and fast on off stump, surprised Mufambisi totally, caught in two minds - pull or hook? - but takes his eyes off it and ends up wafting, gets a touch on that and Baugh collects the catch behind the stumps, all go up in appeal and the bearded Rudi Koertzen raises the finger, Taylor gets another wicket, well bowled, West Indian style lifter

Gentle off break, did nothing dramatic and that was the secret. Ireland pushed at it , expecting it would turn in sharply - why he thought so, only he would know- and ended up playing inside the line. Landed just outside off stump and hit off. As simple as it gets. I think I caught a sheepish grin pastered on Gayle.

headshotImage.caption: Ed Rainsford player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ed Rainsford player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: sharp catch by Bravo at first slip. It was tossed up outside off, turned in a bit and bounced a little. Rainsford goes for a cut and is beaten by the extra bounce. It darted to the left of Bravo who pouches it smartly
And Utseya falls and ZImbabwe have folded up for a meagre 85. He went for a pull  but missed.

gets him with a beauty! Lands on a short of a driveable length in that excellent channel, moves away just enough to draw the edge as Matsikenyeri defends it, Baugh gleefully holds the catch and Smith strikes in his first over, Zimbabwe are halfway over

there you have it, madness, I tell you! Elton Chigumbura went for a stupid swipe the ball before, clearly he didn't learn a thing, tries to smoke a short-of-a-good-length delivery outside off stump into oblivion, doesnt get under it and ends up spooning a simple catch to Taylor at mid-off who only has to take a few steps back and pouch it, Zimbabwe slip even further, how much longer will this innings last?

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha b Bradshaw 1 (8b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 12.5

dismissalComment.html: cleaned up! Bradshaw gets the first wicket with one that lands on middle and off and comes back into Chibhabha, who plays all over it and loses this middle stump

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza b Taylor 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: another batsman's bowled! A fine, swinging delivery that lands on a perfect length outside off stump and jags back in sharply, Masakadza is caught in his crease fishing at it and looks back to see his off stump pegged back, beaten for pace, good strike for Taylor

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor run out (Chanderpaul) 7 (15b 1x4 0x6 23m) SR: 46.66

dismissalComment.html: shortish again, pushed off the back foot to Chanderpaul at short mid-off again and just sets off for the run, utter madness when the balls going right to a fielder, and Chanderpaul swoops in and fires in a direct hit at the nonstriker's end, Taylor is out by a country mile and just keeps on running back to the hut, stupid run, what was he thinking?

dismissalText.commentary: Piet Rinke run out (Hinds) 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: harakiri at Motera! Drifts to middle and off, the straighter ball, works that to midwicket and sets off for the run, Chigumbura sends him back, but Hinds is too smooth here and fires in a throw that catches the big boy Rinke just short of his crease, another run out for Zimbabwe

batsmen.shot: off side drive on front foot

commentTextItems.html: Lara finishes it off in style. Obviously , he doesn't want to mope around in the pavilion for the lunch break. Glides down the track, to the pitch, and deposits it over long-on.

commentPostTextItems.html: After Zimbabwe exploded like cheap party balloons, West Indies, initially, lolled around for some time before Gayle and Lara exploded to wrap-up a facile win.

commentPreTextItems.html: 8 runs needed. Will Lara try to stamp his authority against Utseya. Barring that first ball four, he has not been allowed to get away against the parsimonious offspinner.

commentTextItems.html: There you go, he waltzs down the track and lofts it over widish long-on.

commentPreTextItems.html: Sajan informs me that WI need to get 8 runs in 8 minutes, else they will have to go for the lunch break.

back of length , on the off, pushed to point

lands on the off and middle and spuns past Lara who lets it go through

commentTextItems.html: swept past square-leg . Utseya is bowling pretty well, keeping the great batsman in check.
comes down the track, Utseya drags back the length and Lara has to be contended in just pushing it away
yes sir, single it is. full and outside off, Lara moves towards it to drive it to deep cover. Will keep the strike!

moves back and across, pushes it to cover
